The paper focuses on the application of deep learning, specifically convolutional networks, to solve a non-trivial problem in the telecommunication industry. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of GPUs for training the models also suggests a focus on optimization, which could place the paper in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of an encoding method to transform data into images, which suggests a focus on Computer Vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper mentions the problem of customer churn, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category, as churn prediction is often used as a security measure to prevent fraud.
